  stimulus_text = 'The passage claims that growth of the global middle class is a major driver of rising demand for consumer goods, linking economic expansion in emerging markets to shifting production and trade patterns worldwide. Researchers note that the pattern described above remained consistent across repeated observations, suggesting the finding was not a one-time anomaly. They caution that local conditions can still vary, yet the overall relationship held in each documented case.',
